hands_on_practices.problem:
Let $G$ be a group and let $S_4$ be the symmetric group on 4 elements. Consider a group homomorphism $\phi: G \to S_4$. Suppose there is an element $g \in G$ whose order is exactly 6. What is the set of all possible orders for the element $\phi(g)$ in $S_4$?

A. {1, 2, 3}

B. {1, 2, 3, 4}

C. {1, 2, 3, 6}

D. {2, 3}

E. {1, 6}
